name: Rumah Makan Bidadari ᬭᬸᬫᬄᬫᬓᬦ᭄ᬩᬶᬤᬤᬭᬶ᭟
address: Jl Raya Denpasar Gilimanuk Desa Banyubiru, Kaliakah, Negara, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82218, Indonesia
review 1: they serve halal food with good services. clean area. they also have toilets to shower and make you fresh after land long journey tour from java to bali. big parking lot for buses and cars. last but not least, mushola (place to pray for moslem).
review 2:
came here while on a trip to lombok. average menu, don't expect good taste..you can only get fullness.
Ample parking space, suitable for buses. There are paid toilets, and a prayer room.
In front of the restaurant there is also an Alfamart
review 3: If you need relax after long driver,you can rest in Bidadari restaurant with indonesian food. A little bit spicy, but ok.
review 4: Large parking area,many options food provides here,they have enough toilet for groups,and they have a minimarket ini the restaurant
review 5:
Not the best in around here but the price range is average and actually pretty worth it with the taste of the food
This place is lack of cleaning and air conditioning, and also it is huge open place so kinda lack of privacy but beside that you deserve what you pay
